How to create a virtual environment in python:

1. Create a project folder
syntax: mkdir [your_project_name]
$ mkdir flappy_bird

2. Enter the project folder in visualstudio code
syntax: code [your_project_name]
$ code flappy_bird

--- In vscode do this (using the divscode terminal):
3. Enter the project folder
syntax: cd [your_project_name]
$ cd flappy_bird

4. Create a python virtual environment in your project
syntax: python3 -m venv [your_environment_name]
/flappybird$ python3 -m venv myFlappyBird

5. Activate the environment
/flappybird$ source myFlappyBird/bin/activate

This is to deactivate the environment
/flappybird$ deactivate
